                        "content": "The nurse is reviewing the pathophysiology of pneumonia. The nurse would correctly identify which infection source as an example of hematogenous spread in the pathogenesis of pneumonia?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPneumonia is an acute infection of the lung tissue. Several defense mechanisms protect the lung from infection; however, there are three identified methods by which pathogens reach the lung—aspiration, inhalation, or hematogenous spread. Options 2 and 3 both describe the aspiration route of the pathogenesis of pneumonia, in which normal inhabitants of the oropharynx and nasopharynx reach the lung tissue and cause infection. Option 1 describes the inhalation route. Option 4 describes the hematogenous spread route, as this refers to a primary infection elsewhere in the body, such as endocarditis, spreading to the lung tissue and causing a secondary infection. Therefore, option 4 is correct.",
                        "id": "292a1e129fb34361a48551788dac5381",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d8a1d726850243c387ff256194314023",
                                "content": "A shunt unit exists."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "1ce58d5f109e4f1e8ffbbcb0b40abbec",
                                "content": "Anatomical dead space is present."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b944fed7c2404dd6a5b0479a41fb257a",
                                "content": "Physiological dead space is present."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "5ffd118ed9d74757b589630b8cebe468",
                                "content": "Ventilation-perfusion matching is occurring."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "d8a1d726850243c387ff256194314023",
                                    "content": "A shunt unit exists."
                                },
                                {
