                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is assessing a client presenting with a productive cough, fever, chills, dyspnea, tachypnea, and chest pain that is worse with deep inspiration. Lung auscultation reveals bilateral crackles in the lower lobes. The client’s chest x-ray (CXR) reveals bilateral pulmonary infiltrates in the lower lobes. Which condition would the nurse suspect?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe nurse would suspect pneumonia, as pneumonia is characterized by a cough (which may or may not be productive), fever, chills, dyspnea, tachypnea, and inspiratory chest pain. Lung auscultation will reveal adventitious sounds, such as crackles. Options 1 and 2 are incorrect as the client data suggest a lower respiratory tract infection, and sinusitis and laryngitis are upper respiratory tract infections. Bronchitis and pneumonia share similar symptoms; however, the CXR for a client with acute bronchitis is normal and will not demonstrate infiltrates. Therefore, option 3 is incorrect. A CXR of a client with pneumonia will demonstrate infiltrates or the fluid buildup that occurs in this disease. Therefore, option 4 is correct.",
                        "id": "64812ac55c1c47ea87592ca9d67a594e",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "8592667828624e5f8548a7e47994369c",
                                "content": "Initiate and maintain supplemental oxygen as prescribed."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e5d9a3f9a932416dab1414dc25d823cf",
                                "content": "Plan activities with rest periods to conserve oxygen needs."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "946a89e648854be297fa83342e0b61e8",
                                "content": "Provide nasotracheal suctioning as needed to remove secretions."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "640725f9855b49ffabd0db920594cecc",
                                "content": "Monitor oxygenation (the oxygen saturation [SaO2]) during activity."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "8592667828624e5f8548a7e47994369c",
                                    "content": "Initiate and maintain supplemental oxygen as prescribed."
